content.description: Start under 'How does eat food?'.   Locate very high first bolt up and left on slab.   Climb line of least resistance to that bolt. Watch for loose rock! Finish slab to short head wall. Climb head wall(there is a crack of sorts)  eventually hand traversing right(about 5 feet or so) on a large hand rail to the last bolt then up to anchors
content.location: Just left of 'How does eat food?' and 20 right of Stegosaurus Rex

content.description: Climb directly up to Likin, Lichen, Bush anchors
content.location: Start on small nose between Catfish Cleft and Likin, lichen,Bush

content.description:
Climb 8' to ledge. Probably first and only time I will say it but, Stick clip the first very high bolt. The crux is getting from the ledge to above the first bolt. The wall is slightly overhanging with sparse holds. Very Challenging!

 Has not seen a "red point" yet. I only put 5.12 as a grade because I had to put something. It very well may be harder!

 It may be possible to add a lower bolt and actually be able to clip it..

Locate first bolt. Climb to first bolt on fairly steep rock. It is easier if you climb in from the left. Mantle on big ledge and step right (balancy). Once over second bolt, follow good feet with side pulls (left and right) to last bolt.   Scramble up to anchors.
Climb to first high bolt. Gain large ledge and climb remaining face to shared anchors.
content.protection: 5 or 6 bolts. Anchors shared with route to the left.
content.location: First route north of the water fall

content.description: Start with left hand side pull 6' up. Climb up slightly right on very small, sharp crimps to first bolt (crux, bouldery and hard!). Follow remaining bolts to top of cliff. Watch for loose rock on big ledge half way up.
content.location: Right most of two routes just south of waterfall.

content.description:
Start below first bolt. Climb up to 4th bolt. After 4th bolt and above bulge to anchors up and left. Be nice to the plant that smells like mint!

 Lower/descend down "TR route" to belay the second.
content.location: 12' right of Catfish Cleft around a little nose.

content.description: Start below small easy over lap to first high bolt.  Follow bolts straight up to crack and then continue up face to anchors.   Beware of potential loose rock right of 2nd bolt.
Climb right facing corner to first bolt. Follow bolts up and left to corner and head wall with anchor. Cruxy and balancy getting to second bolt. Then a second crux getting to anchors.
content.location: The left most of two climbs just south of water fall.

content.description: Climb to first bolt (crux if staying directly under the bolt). Scramble to second bolt.   Move left and move over bulge to large horn.   Mantle (crux) and move up. Follow easy slab up straight up from last bolt to the anchors.
content.protection: 3 Bolts and its own 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: Northern most bolted line in this area

content.description: A total of 8 routes right on trail. Currently 5 routes are north of the waterfall and 3 are south of the water fall
